				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">i hate soe<a name="18225"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 31 04 9:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Soe seems to no longer care about the everquest player, they seem to care about gaining more and more new players, an endless amount of newbies and idiots who all want everything given to them.  Soe, being the idiots that they are, gave it to them.  No more CRs or exp loss.  Screw saving up for a bag, you can have one for free.  5 food and drink not enough? Here have 20.  Can’t figure out how to mem spells and set hot keys?  We can do that too.  Boats take to long?  Have gnomish translocaters.  They take to long too? Have PoK.  Don’t want to zone to get your LDoN adventure?  Here’s a magus.  Don’t know when you’re going to get new spells?  Have a reminder message.
<br />

<br />
Soe says that buying everquest goods for IRL money is against the EULA, yet, if you pay them 20$ you get a weight reduction bag.
<br />

<br />
Soe balances classes by taking things away from other classes.  Warriors don’t have enough agro?  Lets nerf rangers!  
<br />

<br />
Soe adds AAs that don’t work, that are bugged, and that have no relevance to the class at hand.
<br />

<br />
Soe’s solution to bugs is adding new and better bugs, and more stuff.  What happened to quality&gt;quantity?
<br />

<br />
They hand out so much stuff that you can level an untwinked character from 1-25 in less then a day. 1-60 in a few months, and you wonder why BoT is so infested with newbies.
<br />

<br />
Why cant soe stop making different everquest games and fix the original.  
<br />

<br />
Soe’s customer support consists of other disgruntled players looking for something new to do.  A year ago you could log on, /who all gm, and 3-5 gms would be on, now, you log in, /petition, and 3-5 days later it gets answered by the guide, the only guide, on your server.
<br />

<br />

<br />
What happened to the skill, the intelligence and the glory of this once wonderful game?  What happened to meeting friends on the boat, learning new languages and role-playing?  What happened to running across the world, unsowed, just to visit qeynos?  What happened to nice people helping nice people, what happened to the level 50 bard helping the level 20 bard get his dark elf mask?  What happened to east commonlands, home of the trader, &quot;3 bags of stuff at torch 2&quot;.  What happened to newbies being content with what they had, as opposed to running to PoK and demanding items and plvling?  
<br />

<br />
What happened to playing everquest?
<br />
</span></td>
