				<td colspan="2"><span>I just hate how they individually and purposefully stretch out the content to literally force you to buy all the expansions.  Kunark and Velious weren't bad, and added some much needed content without any real repercussions for non users.  But now that they basically beefed all the older world zones, especially places like Cazic, Hate, Droga, and Chardok, it makes getting the new expansion equiptment necessary.
<br />

<br />
And the upgrades, are specifically released in each expansion with just enough need as to almost require you to buy it.
<br />

<br />
Luclin:  When in came out the Nexus was the god of transportation, those who didn't have it were stuck using boats, and screwed on trading since the Bazaar was the greatest thing to ever hit the market.  Not to mention kitties and horses.
<br />

<br />
Legacy of Yekesha:  Charm slots, Dyes, a new race and double the bank space were great additions almost guarunteeing a buy, but then the inclusion of cartography sealed the need, players flocked to online downloading.  Oh, and a new race...again.
<br />

<br />
Planes of Power:  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />REQUIRED FOR RAIDING!!!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" />  Absolute dirtiest thing Verant ever did, with the raid window, anyone who didn't have PoP couldn't be invited and basically was excluded from raiding.  Also Transportation became so much easier, and basically knocked Luclin out of usefulness.
<br />

<br />
LDoN:  Well now, let's just make an easier way to get groups and exp, invent a personalized group prancing session.  As if finding a group in an older zone wasn't hard enough already.  Plus who can deny the power of augments, that alone could have forced players to buy.
<br />

<br />
GoD:  The godliest of all items, I mean a 65/30 Berzerker axe with a proc and 300hp, yeah that really compares to old world.  And if the items don't grab you, the unbelieveable AA's and leadership abilities can rope you in.
<br />

<br />
It's all so calculated to make Verant ungodly amounts of money for each release, and the content (storyline, point of each item, quality of the quests) has all gone down as they just try to pump them out like a puppy mill.  And then they screw up with patches and their login server...come on.
<br />

<br />
Personally I really would play on a server that was Pre-Velious only.
<br />

